<h2 class="twikinetRoundedAttachments"><span class="twikinetHeader"><a name="Attendees"></a> Attendees </span></h2>
Matt, Mine, Tim C., Ken, Brian, Gabriele, Rob Q.
<p />
<p />
<h2 class="twikinetRoundedAttachments"><span class="twikinetHeader"><a name="Top_of_Meeting_Business"></a> Top of Meeting Business </span></h2>
<p />
<h3><a name="New_Items_for_OSG_Calendar"></a> New Items for <a href="https://indico.fnal.gov/categoryDisplay.py?categId=86" target="_top">OSG Calendar</a>, </h3>
<h3><a name="Current_plan_for_Newsletter_Arti"></a> Current plan for <a href="https://twiki.grid.iu.edu/bin/view/Management/NewsletterArticles" target="_top">Newsletter Articles</a> </h3>
Please note that all newsletter articles are due around the middle of the month before the targeted newsletter.
<p />
**We want to get an update on the area goals we had established at the staff retreat; these goals are available at <a href="https://osg-docdb.opensciencegrid.org:440/cgi-bin/ShowDocument?docid=1217" target="_top">https://osg-docdb.opensciencegrid.org:440/cgi-bin/ShowDocument?docid=1217</a>
<p />
Also please remember that the next OSG annual report for each area will explicitly state the goals and the results.
<p />
<p />
<h2 class="twikinetRoundedAttachments"><span class="twikinetHeader"><a name="Mine_Altunay_Security"></a> Mine Altunay - Security </span></h2> <ul>
<li> Distributed Computing Access through Federated identities (DCAFI):  <ul>
<li> Phase I: successfully transitioned several experiments over the last weeks. Overall a great success but had some glitches.  <ul>
<li> Dave D. made multiple releases fixing bugs reported by experiments.
</li> <li> Dave D. also gave a talk during NSF <span class="twikiNewLink">CyberSecurity<a href="/bin/edit/Management/CyberSecurity?topicparent=Management.20160831AgendaMinutes" rel="nofollow" title="CyberSecurity (this topic does not yet exist; you can create it)">?</a></span> Summit <a href="http://trustedci.org/s/Computing-Grid-Access-with-Federated-Identity.pdf" target="_top">http://trustedci.org/s/Computing-Grid-Access-with-Federated-Identity.pdf</a>
</li></ul> 
</li> <li> Phase II: accepting other <span class="twikiNewLink">IdPs<a href="/bin/edit/Management/IdPs?topicparent=Management.20160831AgendaMinutes" rel="nofollow" title="IdPs (this topic does not yet exist; you can create it)">?</a></span> than Fermilab <span class="twikiNewLink">IdP<a href="/bin/edit/Management/IdP?topicparent=Management.20160831AgendaMinutes" rel="nofollow" title="IdP (this topic does not yet exist; you can create it)">?</a></span>.
</li></ul> 
</li> <li> Operations <ul>
<li> We had an issue with a user in a disabled VO, who was able to retrieve a certificate signed by <span class="twikiNewLink">DigiCert<a href="/bin/edit/Management/DigiCert?topicparent=Management.20160831AgendaMinutes" rel="nofollow" title="DigiCert (this topic does not yet exist; you can create it)">?</a></span>. We learned that the VO was disabled a long time ago and was never transitioned to CILogon OSG CA. Also, OIM was allowing certificate requests from disabled VOs and had <span class="twikiNewLink">DigiCert<a href="/bin/edit/Management/DigiCert?topicparent=Management.20160831AgendaMinutes" rel="nofollow" title="DigiCert (this topic does not yet exist; you can create it)">?</a></span> as default certificate signer.  <ul>
<li> OIM fixed the bug and set CILogon as default certificate signer.
</li> <li> The issue was communicated to <span class="twikiNewLink">DigiCert<a href="/bin/edit/Management/DigiCert?topicparent=Management.20160831AgendaMinutes" rel="nofollow" title="DigiCert (this topic does not yet exist; you can create it)">?</a></span>. They offered to disable the API entirely for OSG. API was supposed to be used for revocation after the contract ended, but that feature is not working, so we agree on disabling the API entirely. <a href="https://ticket.opensciencegrid.org/30812" target="_top">https://ticket.opensciencegrid.org/30812</a>
</li></ul> 
</li> <li> Vulnerabilities/Incidents: <ul>
<li> Vulnerability in <span class="twikiNewLink">OpenLDAP<a href="/bin/edit/Management/OpenLDAP?topicparent=Management.20160831AgendaMinutes" rel="nofollow" title="OpenLDAP (this topic does not yet exist; you can create it)">?</a></span>, which allows unauthenticated remote <span class="twikiNewLink">DoS<a href="/bin/edit/Management/DoS?topicparent=Management.20160831AgendaMinutes" rel="nofollow" title="DoS (this topic does not yet exist; you can create it)">?</a></span>, by sending a tampered message and making <span class="twikiNewLink">OpenLDAP<a href="/bin/edit/Management/OpenLDAP?topicparent=Management.20160831AgendaMinutes" rel="nofollow" title="OpenLDAP (this topic does not yet exist; you can create it)">?</a></span> daemon crash. <ul>
<li> Jeny Performed testing on OSG BDII ITB regarding the vulnerability announced in <span class="twikiNewLink">OpenLDAP<a href="/bin/edit/Management/OpenLDAP?topicparent=Management.20160831AgendaMinutes" rel="nofollow" title="OpenLDAP (this topic does not yet exist; you can create it)">?</a></span>.  However, since OSG BDII is coming to its end-of-life, GOC and OSG Security decided to do not apply the security updates. <a href="https://ticket.opensciencegrid.org/30708" target="_top">https://ticket.opensciencegrid.org/30708</a>
</li></ul> 
</li> <li> Vulnerabilities reported in Perfsonar: Shawn <span class="twikiNewLink">McKee<a href="/bin/edit/Management/McKee?topicparent=Management.20160831AgendaMinutes" rel="nofollow" title="McKee (this topic does not yet exist; you can create it)">?</a></span> confirmed that the version installed in OSG's Perfsonar instances is 3.5.1.4 contained the security updates <a href="https://ticket.opensciencegrid.org/30595" target="_top">https://ticket.opensciencegrid.org/30595</a>
</li></ul> 
</li> <li> Jeny gave a talk at WISE Workshop during XSEDE’16 about how OSG approaches Operational Security <a href="https://wiki.geant.org/download/attachments/59248511/WISE_2016_Talk_OSGSec.pdf?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1468870769835&amp;api=v2" target="_top">https://wiki.geant.org/download/attachments/59248511/WISE_2016_Talk_OSGSec.pdf?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1468870769835&amp;api=v2</a>
</li></ul> 
</li> <li> HEPCloud Risk assessment
</li> <li> Discussion about Singularity <ul>
<li> Seems to provide reasonable isolation, protection from escalation to root
</li> <li> Open questions remain about traceability / accountability / logging in the context of OSG and our implementation
</li></ul> 
</li> <li> Security Drill: Did not have success submitting jobs following different set of instructions. Anand and Jeny have worked on this. No success so far.
</li> <li> Globus GSSAPI Name compatibility (strict mode) implementation coming into OSG Software stack.  <ul>
<li> Jeny made a quick verification over the certificates used in OSG services: myosg, bdii, repo., ticket, gratiaweb,… and send recommendations to GOC to update the certificates
</li></ul> 
</li> <li> Security Training for VOs  <ul>
<li> Updated version.
</li> <li> Upcoming security training for 2 new VOs.
</li></ul> 
</li> <li> So far Frank, Susan, Mine and Brian agreed that Mine will shift her focus on HEPCloud and Susan will start spending more time on OSG. Specifically Mine will continue to report effort to operational security and the IR, and Susan will be responsible for the new goals such as software assurance and program evaluation. 
</li></ul> 
<p />
<p />
<h2 class="twikinetRoundedAttachments"><span class="twikinetHeader"><a name="Stakeholder_Request_Management_G"></a> Stakeholder Request Management - Gabriele Garzoglio </span></h2>
<p />
<a href="https://jira.opensciencegrid.org/secure/Dashboard.jspa?selectPageId=10030" target="_top">https://jira.opensciencegrid.org/secure/Dashboard.jspa?selectPageId=10030</a>
<p />
<h2 class="twikinetRoundedAttachments"><span class="twikinetHeader"><a name="Minutes"></a> Minutes </span></h2>
<p />
<p />
Key Initiatives <ol>
<li> HEP Cloud Risk Trash/Trash/Assessment to be delivered in 1 week.
</li> <li> Singularity (container technology to substitute gLExec) provides user isolation; investigating traceability, accountability and logging.
</li> <li> Security Drill: slow progress: facing issues with job submission
</li></ol> 
<p />
Top Issues / Concerns <ol>
<li> Adjusting effort on Security at Fermilab to align with Susan taking leadership. Agreeing with relevant parties on priorities of Fermilab effort and Susan's effort.
</li></ol> 
<p />
Key Accomplishments <ol>
<li> DCAFI project (transition of FIFE VOs to CILogon basic CA) is successful. Presented at the NSF <span class="twikiNewLink">CyberSecurity<a href="/bin/edit/Management/CyberSecurity?topicparent=Management.20160831AgendaMinutes" rel="nofollow" title="CyberSecurity (this topic does not yet exist; you can create it)">?</a></span> Summit. Currently using only Fermilab <span class="twikiNewLink">IdP<a href="/bin/edit/Management/IdP?topicparent=Management.20160831AgendaMinutes" rel="nofollow" title="IdP (this topic does not yet exist; you can create it)">?</a></span>: proposed Phase II to accept other <span class="twikiNewLink">IdPs<a href="/bin/edit/Management/IdPs?topicparent=Management.20160831AgendaMinutes" rel="nofollow" title="IdPs (this topic does not yet exist; you can create it)">?</a></span>.
</li></ol> 
